    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="520">
      <subfield code="a">We examine the hypothesis that inflation is primarily driven by vacuum energy at a scale indicated by gauge coupling unification. Concretely, we consider a class of hybrid inflation models wherein the vacuum energy associated with a grand unified theory condensate provides the dominant energy during inflation, while a second “inflaton” scalar slow rolls. We show that it is possible to obtain significant tensor-to-scalar ratios while fitting the observed spectral index.</subfield>
      <subfield code="9">APS</subfield>
    </datafield>
